      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON GUITAR (4) has missed the frame at his last couple of starts but just a few runs back broke the clock when winning over 545m at Ballarat, taking a Special conditions race in a flying 30.65. Rates on top and can find winning form again. ULENTA BALE (8) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing second and beaten 2 lengths (27.31) behind Doongalla Rocket at Horsham. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Expected to be in this for a long way. KIA KEEPING (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (29.78) in a OPEN at Mt Gambier. Shapes as one to consider. ZIPPING SINGH (3) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
